
"smart_sources:Research/@yildiz_wild_2015.md": {"path":"Research/@yildiz_wild_2015.md","last_embed":{"hash":null},"embeddings":{},"last_read":{"hash":"a3vfpy","at":1774951884832},"class_name":"SmartSource","last_import":{"mtime":1774951829451,"size":2614,"at":1774951884832,"hash":"a3vfpy"},"blocks":{"#---frontmatter---":[1,69],"#Wild Edible Mushrooms as a Natural Source of Phenolics and Antioxidants":[71,75],"#Wild Edible Mushrooms as a Natural Source of Phenolics and Antioxidants#{1}":[73,75]},"outlinks":[{"title":"Author/Oktay Yıldız","target":"Author/Oktay Yıldız","line":54},{"title":"Author/Oktay Yildiz","target":"Author/Oktay Yildiz","line":55},{"title":"Author/Zehra Can","target":"Author/Zehra Can","line":56},{"title":"Author/Zehra Can","target":"Author/Zehra Can","line":57},{"title":"Author/Abdul Qayoom Laghari","target":"Author/Abdul Qayoom Laghari","line":58},{"title":"Author/Abdul Qayoom Laghari","target":"Author/Abdul Qayoom Laghari","line":59},{"title":"Author/Hüseyin Şahin","target":"Author/Hüseyin Şahin","line":60},{"title":"Author/Hüseyin Şahin","target":"Author/Hüseyin Şahin","line":61},{"title":"Author/Huseyin Sahin","target":"Author/Huseyin Sahin","line":62},{"title":"Author/Meltem Malkoç","target":"Author/Meltem Malkoç","line":63},{"title":"Author/Meltem Malkoç","target":"Author/Meltem Malkoç","line":64},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/yildiz_wild_2015/yildiz_wild_2015.pdf","line":66}],"metadata":{"id":"yildiz_wild_2015","type":"article-journal","title":"Wild Edible Mushrooms as a Natural Source of Phenolics and Antioxidants","issued":{"date-parts":[[2015]]},"DOI":"10.1111/jfbc.12107","container-title":"Journal of Food Biochemistry","abstract":"The purpose of this study was to evaluate the total phenolic contents, antioxidant properties and phenolic composition of four edible mushroom species, Ganoderma lucidum, Morchella esculenta, Lentinula edodes and Hericium erinaceus. Extraction of phenolic compounds was carried out in an ultrasonic bath. Total phenolic contents were determined using Folin–Ciocalteu’s reagent and the results were calculated using gallic acid equivalents (GAE). Ferric reducing antioxidant power and 2,2-diphenyl-1-picrylhydrazyl free radical-scavenging antioxidant activities were also measured and Trolox was used as positive control. Phenolic composition was determined using high-performance liquid chromatography and comparisons with standards. Total phenolic contents were highest in G. lucidum (26.40 mg GAE/g), followed by M. esculenta, L. edodes and H. erinaceus. The same trend was observed in individual phenolic composition and antioxidant activities, these also were higher in G. lucidum compared with the other species.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Yıldız","given":"Oktay","literal":""},{"family":"Yildiz","given":"Oktay","literal":""},{"family":"Can","given":"Zehra","literal":""},{"family":"Can","given":"Zehra","literal":""},{"family":"Laghari","given":"Abdul Qayoom","literal":""},{"family":"Laghari","given":"Abdul Qayoom","literal":""},{"family":"Şahin","given":"Hüseyin","literal":""},{"family":"Şahin","given":"Hüseyin","literal":""},{"family":"Sahin","given":"Huseyin","literal":""},{"family":"Malkoç","given":"Meltem","literal":""},{"family":"Malkoç","given":"Meltem","literal":""}],"citation-key":"yildiz_wild_2015","year":"2015","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Wild Edible Mushrooms as a Natural Source of Phenolics and Antioxidants"],"author-links":["[[Author/Oktay Yıldız]]","[[Author/Oktay Yildiz]]","[[Author/Zehra Can]]","[[Author/Zehra Can]]","[[Author/Abdul Qayoom Laghari]]","[[Author/Abdul Qayoom Laghari]]","[[Author/Hüseyin Şahin]]","[[Author/Hüseyin Şahin]]","[[Author/Huseyin Sahin]]","[[Author/Meltem Malkoç]]","[[Author/Meltem Malkoç]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/yildiz_wild_2015/yildiz_wild_2015.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},
